# Security Rules (Shannon Pro)

## Pre-Commit Security Checks

Before marking ANY code change complete, verify:

### Input Validation
- ALL user input is validated and sanitized at the entry point
- SQL queries use parameterized statements (never string concatenation)
- HTML output is escaped (no innerHTML with user data)
- File paths are sanitized against path traversal (no `../`)
- URLs are validated before fetching (no SSRF)
- Deserialization only accepts expected types

### Authentication & Authorization
- Auth checks exist on EVERY endpoint that modifies data
- JWT tokens are validated with algorithm pinning (no `alg: none`)
- API keys and secrets are in environment variables (never hardcoded)
- Session tokens have sufficient entropy (≥128 bits)
- Password hashing uses bcrypt/argon2 (never MD5/SHA1)
- Rate limiting on authentication endpoints

### Security Headers
```
Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'
Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
X-Frame-Options: DENY
Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
```

### Secrets
- No API keys, passwords, or tokens in code
- No credentials in git history
- Environment-specific config via `.env` files (gitignored)

